          <Comment>This sequence change creates a premature translational stop signal (p.Gln371Lysfs*48) in the CLCN1 gene. It is expected to result in an absent or disrupted protein product. Loss-of-function variants in CLCN1 are known to be pathogenic (PMID: 17932099, 22094069, 23739125). This variant is present in population databases (no rsID available, gnomAD 0.007%). This premature translational stop signal has been observed in individual(s) with autosomal recessive myotonia congenita (PMID: 21221019). For these reasons, this variant has been classified as Pathogenic.</Comment>
